---
// Storytelling con parallax y reveals por línea.
---

<section
  id="experiencia"
  class="relative flex min-h-screen flex-col justify-center overflow-hidden bg-[var(--bg-deep,#050505)] py-32"
>
  <!-- Mancha de pintura parallax -->
  <div
    data-parallax="0.2"
    class="pointer-events-none absolute -left-20 top-20 h-80 w-80 rounded-full bg-[var(--accent)] opacity-[0.12] blur-[120px]"
  >
  </div>
  <div
    data-parallax="-0.15"
    class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-10 bottom-10 h-96 w-96 rounded-full bg-[var(--accent-deep,#fc277c)] opacity-[0.1] blur-[140px]"
  >
  </div>

  <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6">
    <p class="font-tag text-base tracking-wide text-[var(--accent)]">// la experiencia</p>

    <h2 class="display mt-4 text-4xl leading-tight text-white md:text-7xl">
      <span data-split class="block">Entrás por un corte.</span>
      <span data-split class="block">
        Salís siendo <span class="text-[var(--accent)]">otro</span>.
      </span>
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-14 grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-3">
      {
        [
          { t: "Sin apuro", d: "Tu turno es tuyo. Acá nadie te corre de la silla." },
          { t: "Música y birra", d: "Ambiente street, buena música y la previa perfecta." },
          { t: "Detalle de rey", d: "Cada corte cierra con un toque que se nota." },
        ].map((b) => (
          <div data-reveal class="border-l-2 border-[var(--accent)] pl-5">
            <h3 class="display text-2xl text-white">{b.t}</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/60">{b.d}</p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
